        "id": 1904238,
        "name": "David Bueker",
        "username": "David_Bu3ker",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/david_bu3ker/{size}/319725_2.png",
        "created_at": "2016-04-07T23:08:19.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p><a href=\"http://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=2002837&amp;iNote=5613747\"><strong>2012 Schloss Gobelsburg Riesling Tradition</strong></a> <em>- Austria, Nieder\u00f6sterreich, Kamptal (4/5/2016)</em><br>\nI followed this wine through an entire meal of numerous small courses, so it was faced with a wide variety of foods. It performed admirably with everything from a white asparagus dish, to a duck ravioli in dashi broth, even managing a decent pairing with foie gras. The richness of the wine played well with heavier dishes, while its resolutely dry style was a perfect foil for the lighter items. Peachy, spicy flavors, and a wide range of aromatics made for a wine that was also very interesting on its own. Even better was the $45 US equivalent pricing on the Polish restaurant wine list!</p>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"http://www.cellartracker.com/\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
